{"key":"post-12678077","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12678077</id>\n<content>It's probably not condensation.&amp;nbsp; I suspect you're pumping in way too much moisture.&amp;nbsp; If the air is already at 100%, it can't absorb any more, thus the extra moisture falls onto your substrate like rain.&amp;nbsp; In my mini-greenhouses, I only use a coolmist, no ultrasonic, and the cool mist only runs for one minute on, five to six minutes off.&amp;nbsp; This results in a humidity in the 90s.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Be sure to have lots of holes and/or slits cut in the plastic to allow for fresh air to enter and exit.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Calibrate your hygrometer by wrapping it up in a damp towel for an hour to make sure it reads 99%.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12678101</next>\n<prev>12677802</prev>\n<first>12677143</first>\n<last>12692051</last>\n<when>1275585589</when>\n<utime>06/03/10 08:19 PM</utime>\n</post>"}